 chess players build a communal identity. Full of idiosyncratic characters and dramatic gameplay, Players and Pawns is a celebration of the fascinating world of serious chess.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aChessxPsychological aspects. 0aChessxSocial aspects. 0aChessxTournaments. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  achess, community, culture, interpersonal, communication, discourse, sociology, research, fieldwork, academic, scholarly, educational, sports, games, opponents, theory, strategy, queen, pawn, king, knight, castle, challenges, traditions, communal, identity, pawns, psychology, philosophy, tournaments, competition, professional, international, global, board game.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226265032423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226265032/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles